sentences: Charles Burchill (born 27 November 1959) is a Scottish musician and composer, best known as the guitarist of Simple Minds.
This style was most apparent on 1982's New Gold Dream (81/82/83/84).
From 1983's album Sparkle in the Rain onwards the group evolved a different style, bringing Burchill's playing more into the foreground.
As well as providing guitar, Burchill played the violin and saxophone on the band's first three studio albums and took over most studio keyboard duties following the 1989 departure of Mick MacNeil.
